= Fisheye Lens VEX =
#context: vop
#type: node

"""A CVEX lens shader that applies fisheye distortion for Mantra rendering."""

== Overview ==

Fisheye Lens VEX is a CVEX lens shader that remaps rays from a standard perspective camera into a fisheye projection. Assign it to a Mantra camera's lens shader parameter.

The shader supports full 180° fisheye by default, with an optional circular mask to crop the image to the fisheye disc.

@parameters

fov:
    #id: fov
    Field of view in degrees. Default is `180`.

mask:
    #id: mask
    When enabled, pixels outside the circular fisheye boundary are masked out (made invalid).
